      • extractMassiveHistoryToFile

        public void extractMassiveHistoryToFile(java.util.List<java.lang.String> appIds,
                                        java.lang.Integer year,
                                        java.lang.Integer month)
        This method fetches the application data within appIds of year-month into file outfileBInstinct in a massive manner.

        Number of blocksize application data will be accessed at each time. And it is suggested to fetch less than 500 sets of data at a time due to possible heavy workload of SQLServer and the intensive memory consumption of DataContainer.

        All failed appIds will be stored in file outfileFailedAppIds with their reasons stored in file outfileFailedReasons.

        Parameters:
        appIds - the list storing historical application ids to fetch.
        year - the year of application data to fetch.
        month - the month of application data to fetch.

      • extractHistoryToFile

        public void extractHistoryToFile(java.util.List<java.lang.String> appIds,
                                 java.lang.Integer year,
                                 java.lang.Integer month)
        This method fetches the application data within appIds of year-month into file outfileBInstinct one by one. All failed appIds will be stored in outfileFailedAppIds with their reasons stored in file outfileFailedReasons.
        Parameters:
        appIds - the list storing historical application ids to fetch.
        year - the year of application data to fetch.
        month - the month of application data to fetch.

      • clearHistoryFiles

        public java.lang.Boolean clearHistoryFiles(java.lang.Integer year,
                                           java.lang.Integer month)
        This method deletes the existing old history files of year-month, including outfileBInstinct, outfileFailedAppIds, outfileFailedReasons and outfileAppIds.
        Parameters:
        year - the year of application data to fetch.
        month - the month of application data to fetch.
        Returns:
        true when some of the files is deleted.

        false when no file is deleted.
